# --- Database (Neon + Vercel) ---
#
# Option A — Same DATABASE_URL on Production and Preview (one Neon database):
#   Production (main):  do NOT set DB_SCHEMA  → app uses PostgreSQL schema `public`
#   Preview (develop):  DB_SCHEMA=test        → app uses PostgreSQL schema `test`
#
# Option B — Different Neon branches / URLs:
#   Omit DB_SCHEMA on both; use main-branch URL for Production and develop-branch URL for Preview.
#
# After changing Drizzle models, push from your machine (same URL is OK for Option A):
#   npm run db:push:prod     — updates `public` (`.env.production.local`)
#   npm run db:push:preview  — updates `test`   (`.env.preview.local` should include DB_SCHEMA=test for the app; push uses schemaFilter "test")
#
# One-time admin per logical database / schema: set ADMIN_BOOTSTRAP_PASSWORD, then:
#   npm run seed:admin:prod    or    npm run seed:admin:preview
# For Preview with Option A, put DB_SCHEMA=test in `.env.preview.local` before seeding.
